declarations.comments:
Creates a HugeNum from a Number.
May lose precision if the argument is too large.
declarations.title: toNumber

declarations.comments:
Create a HugeNum from a String.
Strings should be in the form of Purescript Numbers. For example,
fromString "123.456" => Just (HugeNum 123.456)
declarations.title: fromString

declarations.comments:
## Miscellaneous easily-defined functions
Limits the number of digits past the decimal.
declarations.title: truncate

declarations.comments: Returns the integer part of a HugeNum. Does the same as flooring.
declarations.title: integerPart

declarations.comments: Returns the fractional part of a HugeNum.
declarations.title: fractionalPart

declarations.comments: Raise a HugeNum to an integer power.
declarations.title: pow
